com.centurylink.mdw.annotations

Annotation Type Monitor


  • @Documented
 @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Monitor

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.Class<? extends Monitor> category
      This represents the type of monitor to (optionally register).
      java.lang.String value
      Value is the monitor label.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean defaultEnabled
      Recommended practice is to leave this set to false, and then enable per activity in MDW Studio or MDWHub.
      java.lang.String defaultOptions
      Default value for user-entered options for this monitor.
      java.lang.String enablementCategory 

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract java.lang.String value
        Value is the monitor label.

      • category

        public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends Monitor> category
        This represents the type of monitor to (optionally register).

      • defaultEnabled

        public abstract boolean defaultEnabled
        Recommended practice is to leave this set to false, and then enable per activity in MDW Studio or MDWHub. This way only designated activities will trigger this monitor. If defaultEnabled is set to true, this monitor is enabled unless explicitly deselected in MDW Studio/Hub.
        Default:
        false

      • enablementCategory

        public abstract java.lang.String enablementCategory
        Default:
        ""

      • defaultOptions

        public abstract java.lang.String defaultOptions
        Default value for user-entered options for this monitor. The value entered in MDW Studio/Hub is available as the forth column in the JSONArray value from attribute "monitors" in the runtimeContext.
        Default:
        ""
